<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1436,1214,1670]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1431,1455]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Galil, B. S." box="[323,462,1430,1454]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="279 - 320" refId="ref47241" refString="Galil, B. S. (2009) An examination of the genus Philyra Leach, 1817 (Crustacea, Decapoda, Leucosiidae) with description of seven new genera and six new species. Zoosystema, 31 (2), 279 - 320." type="journal article" year="2009">Galil (2009)</bibRefCitation>
recently partly revised the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Leach, 1817" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1817" box="[849,1084,1430,1454]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Philyra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[849,933,1430,1454]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Philyra</emphasis>
Leach, 1817
</taxonomicName>
, introducing seven new genera within the genus. She clarified the taxonomic position of the some important species, which have already been known from the Persian Gulf. For instance, several authors (e. g. 
<bibRefCitation author="Alcock, A." box="[893,1041,1502,1526]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="134 - 296" refId="ref44182" refString="Alcock, A. (1896) Material for a carcinological Fauna of India. No. 2: The Brachyura Oxystomata. Journal of the Asiatic Society of Bengal, 65 (2), 134 - 296." type="journal article" year="1896">Alcock 1896</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Guinot, D." box="[1054,1206,1502,1526]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="235 - 352" refId="ref47607" refString="Guinot, D. (1967) La faune carcinologique (Crustacea, Brachyura) de l'Ocean Indien occidental et de la Mer Rouge. Catalogue remarques biogeographiques et bibliographie. Memoires de l'Institut fondamental d'Afrique noire, 77, 235 - 352." type="journal article" year="1967">Guinot, 1967</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Basson, P. W. &amp; Burchard, J. E. &amp; Hardy, J. T. &amp; Price, A. R. G." box="[1218,1431,1502,1526]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" refId="ref45702" refString="Basson, P. W., Burchard, J. E., Hardy, J. T. &amp; Price, A. R. G. (1977) Biotopes of the Western Arabian Gulf: Marine life and environments of Saudi Arabia. ARAMCO, Dept. of Loss Prevention and environmental affairs, Dhahran: 289 pp." type="book" year="1977">
Basson 
<emphasis box="[1307,1357,1502,1526]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">et al</emphasis>
. 1977
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Titgen, R. H." box="[151,287,1538,1562]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" refId="ref53402" refString="Titgen, R. H. (1982) The systematics and ecology of the Decapods of Dubai, and their zoogeographic relationships to the Persian Gulf and the Western Indian Ocean. Unpublished doctoral thesis, Texas A &amp; M University, 292 pp." type="book" year="1982">Titgen 1982</bibRefCitation>
) have recorded 
<taxonomicName authority="De Haan, 1847" authorityName="De Haan" authorityYear="1847" box="[469,853,1538,1563]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Philyra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="platycheir">
<emphasis box="[469,674,1539,1563]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Philyra platycheir</emphasis>
De Haan, 1847
</taxonomicName>
, from the Persian Gulf and Tirmizi &amp; Ghani (1986) from 
<collectingCountry box="[215,313,1574,1598]" name="Pakistan" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
, but 
<bibRefCitation author="Galil, B. S." box="[372,512,1574,1598]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="279 - 320" refId="ref47241" refString="Galil, B. S. (2009) An examination of the genus Philyra Leach, 1817 (Crustacea, Decapoda, Leucosiidae) with description of seven new genera and six new species. Zoosystema, 31 (2), 279 - 320." type="journal article" year="2009">Galil (2009)</bibRefCitation>
introduced the new genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Galil, 2009" authorityName="Galil" authorityYear="2009" box="[827,1054,1574,1598]" class="Malacostraca" family="Leucosiidae" genus="Hiplyra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[827,914,1574,1598]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Hiplyra</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Galil, B. S." box="[923,1054,1574,1598]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="279 - 320" refId="ref47241" refString="Galil, B. S. (2009) An examination of the genus Philyra Leach, 1817 (Crustacea, Decapoda, Leucosiidae) with description of seven new genera and six new species. Zoosystema, 31 (2), 279 - 320." type="journal article" year="2009">Galil, 2009</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, for the species and restricted its distribution to 
<collectingCountry box="[318,385,1611,1634]" name="Japan" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Japan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[397,464,1610,1634]" name="China" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">China</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[521,607,1610,1634]" name="Taiwan" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Ruppell" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[619,821,1611,1635]" class="Malacostraca" family="Leucosiidae" genus="Hiplyra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="variegata">
<emphasis box="[619,821,1611,1635]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Hiplyra variegata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the species distributed in the western Indian Ocean including the Persian Gulf, while 
<taxonomicName authorityName="De Haan" authorityYear="1847" box="[529,677,1646,1670]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Philyra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="platycheir">
<emphasis box="[529,549,1647,1670]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[563,677,1646,1670]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">platycheir</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not present in the Indian Ocean.
</paragraph>
